HEADWORD: Myriad
<hw>Myr"i*ad</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, <?/, fr.
<?/ numberless, pl. <?/ ten thousand: cf. F. <ets>myriade</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The number of ten thousand; ten thousand persons or
things.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An immense number; a very great many; an
indefinitely large number.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Myriad</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Myriad
<hw>Myr"i*ad</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Consisting of a very great, but
indefinite, number; <as>as, <ex>myriad</ex> stars</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

